Endpoint Security 

Course: Endpoint Security
Duration: 27 Hours
Labs Completed: 31
Level: Beginner ‚Üí SOC Foundations
Focus: Endpoint Defense, OS Security, Network Attacks, Threat Mitigation

üìå Overview

This course provided hands-on foundational training in endpoint security, operating systems, network defense, and threat mitigation. The curriculum focused on defending systems at the network edge, where attacks most frequently occur, and emphasized real-world attack techniques, vulnerabilities, and defensive controls used by Security Operations Centers (SOC).

Through theory, labs, and simulations, I developed practical skills in endpoint hardening, threat detection, system monitoring, and incident prevention across Windows, Linux, wired, and wireless environments.

üéØ Core Skills Gained

Endpoint threat detection and mitigation

Windows and Linux system security

Network and wireless attack analysis

Host-based intrusion prevention

Malware identification and containment

Secure configuration and hardening

Log analysis and system monitoring

SOC-relevant investigation methodology

